Rating: 4
Excellent! I did it for Valentines' Dinner. This was my first time cooking duck and it was very easy and very tasty. (and fast, compared with other duck recipes). I couldn't get endives, so as a side dich I did straw potato pancakes (cut the potatoes into juliane strips, dry them, sautee them as little cakes in a mix of butter and vegetable oil) which added crunchiness to the recipe. I served the sauce in a separate bowl, so each of of us could decide how much sauce we wanted.

