Rating: 3
This made a wonderful holiday-time dinner for two. I considered halving the sauce recipe, but didn't, and it didn't seem to be too much at all when cooking only two duck breasts. The amount of sugar seemed like a lot to me, so I cut back on that just a bit, though now that I've made it, I don't think it would be too sweet if prepared exactly as written. I was surprised the braised endive still maintained a little crunch and retained its own distinctive flavor in spite of the sauce and the braising.

